      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted hemolysis index within 20% of experimental measurements across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis predictions compared against Malinauskas et al. (2017) experimental data. Maximum relative error of 14.7% observed at the 6 LPM / 2500 RPM condition. All five operating points within the 20% acceptance band. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly map to clinical hemolysis endpoints used in regulatory submission.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH) are the primary QoIs. Both are directly referenced in FDA guidance for blood-contacting device submissions and are the same metrics used in bench testing. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
