      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 3 for medium model influence.",
      "rationale": "Use error factor is scoped out of the required assessment at Model Risk Level 2 with medium model influence. No structured level assessment is required or performed. Documented as not-assessed per project credibility plan."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "factorAcceptanceCriteria": "Qualitative expert review of turbulence model and hemolysis power-law formulation suitability for pump flow regimes.",
      "rationale": "A qualitative assessment was conducted by the modelling team and an independent CFD expert reviewer to evaluate the suitability of the SST k-omega turbulence closure and the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model for the centrifugal pump flow regime. The review considered published literature on turbulence model performance in rotating machinery with transitional flow, the sensitivity of the hemolysis exponent to shear stress distributions in the volute and impeller passages, and the known conservatism of the power-law formulation relative to mechanistic red blood cell damage models. The expert panel reached consensus that the selected model form is fit for purpose for identifying relative worst-case operating conditions at MRL 2, acknowledging that absolute hemolysis magnitude predictions carry higher uncertainty. This qualitative determination supports the overall Accepted outcome without requiring a formal numerical gradation assignment for this factor at the current model risk level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key material properties and boundary condition inputs documented with traceability to measurement sources.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity modelled as Newtonian with dynamic viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s per ISO 10993-4 reference values. Rotational speed and flow rate inputs derived from pump test reports with calibrated instrumentation. All inputs documented in the simulation data package. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for computational-only assessment where physical sample variability is addressed through sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Test samples factor is not applicable to the computational assessment workflow at MRL 2. Physical sample variability in the FDA benchmark study is addressed through the published experimental uncertainty bounds used in output comparison. Documented as not-assessed per credibility plan."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
